heaviest_rainfall.status: Record amounts of rain fell over 31.0 hours today with a total accumulation of 23.86mm.  It fell at 8.3 mm per hour at times and ranked 7th from our records.  The largest amount of rain ever recorded is on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm fell at a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour over the 144.8 hour event.

heaviest_rainrate.status: The 2nd ranked rain rate was recorded today with a peak rate of 27.6mm per hour, highlighting an extreme precipitation event.  5.63mm of rain fell during the storm's 2.1 hours length.  34.3mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: Today, one rain storm lasted for 31.0 hours (ranking 7th for longest storm from our records).  It accumulated 23.86mm of rain and it fell at 8.3mm per hour at times.  A relentless rainstorm took place on 09 November 2025, it lasted 144.8 hours and it delivered 47.89mm of rain at a maximum rate of 24.6mm per hour.
